ul.li: Independent State: Each struct file has its own f_pos, allowing independent read/write offsets.
Shared Behavior: All instances of the device share the same file_operations jump table.
VTable Security: f_op is usually const in kernel code to prevent rootkit hooking via pointer hijacking.

g.text: Total: ~248 bytes (size varies by kernel config)
0x20 | struct file_operations* | f_op // Pointer to table
0x08 | struct cdev* | i_cdev // Points to our cdev
file_operations is exactly a C++ vtable
